1
00:00:07,670 --> 00:00:09,540
交易所主席简加奇尝试

2
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:12,800
减低市场对霸菱倒闭的事的恐惧

3
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:18,710
...denied reports the British banking system is about to collapse.
他向国会发言否认报导  英国银行体系将崩溃

4
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,180
According to him, Barings' failure is a unique situation,...
他说霸菱银行是个别例子

5
00:00:22,270 --> 00:00:26,150
...which he blames on the actions of a rogue trader in Singapore.
是由新加坡的一名股票经纪造成

6
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:31,630
Estimates of potential losses range from 800 million to over one billion pounds.
估计今次损失达八亿至十亿英镑

7
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:39,570
股坛狙击手

8
00:00:52,550 --> 00:00:54,510
Look at that!
看看...

9
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:56,580
Will you fuckin' look at that!
你看清楚

10
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:59,620
- What, with the black guy? - Yeah.
是个黑人吗？

11
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:03,900
It's a shame. She looks well spoken for.
真可惜，她看来不错

12
00:01:04,710 --> 00:01:07,100
Never know your luck, though. Eh, mate?
别笑人，小心倒霉

13
00:01:07,190 --> 00:01:10,900
- Think I'll give her the treatment! - No, Steve, no. Don't do that.
我会好好待她                                    不，史提

14
00:01:10,990 --> 00:01:13,900
- No, you're all right. - Don't do that. Steve. Steve!
你不会有事                   史提，不要

15
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:19,740
Hello, love. I've got something to show ya.
嗨，靓女，我有东西给你看

16
00:01:23,790 --> 00:01:26,900
Are you out of your mind or what? You fuckin' little prick!
你疯了吗？

17
00:01:26,990 --> 00:01:28,940
And I mean little!
别在众人面前出丑

18
00:01:29,030 --> 00:01:31,420
Don't judge a book by its cover, sweetheart.
不要单看外表

19
00:01:31,510 --> 00:01:34,310
- You're out of your league, arsehole. - Calm down.
你太幸运       什么？只是对女士说

20
00:01:34,390 --> 00:01:36,140
Fuck off or you're dead!
滚开，你死定

21
00:01:36,230 --> 00:01:39,020
- I want you out of here, now. - He's really sorry.
立刻出去...                                     他有悔意了

22
00:01:39,110 --> 00:01:43,220
He's pissed. He meant no disrespect. That's the last thing on anybody's mind.
他喝醉，不想惹事的              也不能责骂

23
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:45,820
Tell him if he doesn't put that thing away,...
叫他把那东西收起，否则

24
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:48,780
...I'll rip it off and shove it down his fuckin' throat!
怎样？      我会扭着他脖子

25
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:52,410
Do your flies up, you fuckin' animal. You almost gave me a heart attack.
你这疯狂动物吓坏了我

26
00:01:53,910 --> 00:01:57,450
Just leave it. It's not worth it!
别管他             他不值

27
00:01:57,540 --> 00:01:59,740
He's done it again. I had to pull him off!
再来我便送他到监狱

28
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:01,580
Fuckin' right laugh!
我不怕的   尽管来

29
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:12,500
Nick! Nick!
尼克

30
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,570
You all right? Nick!
尼克，没事吧？

31
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:34,250
It was thanks to Maggie Thatcher opening up the City of London...
谢谢戴卓尔夫人开辟了伦敦市

32
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:39,810
...that yours truly from Watford came to be working for a posh outfit like Barings.
让我们为霸菱工作

33
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,580
（霸菱银行）

34
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:45,490
That was me lying on the floor, if you hadn't guessed. Nick Leeson.
这不是真心话   尼克利森，

35
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:47,570
You've probably heard about me.
应听闻我的名字

36
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:54,500
Barings was the oldest private bank in the world.
霸菱是全球最悠久银行

37
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:59,130
They financed the Louisiana Purchase back in eighteen hundred and something.
在1803年   支持美国购入路易斯安纳州

38
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:02,290
They even had the Queen as a customer!
历史真长久  女皇都是顾客

39
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:08,850
I was just a humble clerk.
我只是文员

40
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:10,850
But not for long, I hoped.
希望快晋升

41
00:03:11,620 --> 00:03:13,490
Car crash.
汽车意外

42
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:16,730
I hit my head on the back of the seat and broke my nose.
我撞到头部和鼻骨折了

43
00:03:16,820 --> 00:03:20,970
Everybody else was all right cos they were wearing their, um... seat belts.
其他人戴安全带，所以没事

44
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:23,050
Poor chap!
真可怜

45
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:29,010
Nick, I know you're keen to get out of the back office and onto the trading floor,...
尼克   知道你希望在股市交易所工作

46
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:32,090
...but in the meantime something else has come up.
但有事发生了

47
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,690
We've got problems in our Jakarta office.
雅加达的公司出事

48
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:37,850
We need someone to go out there and sort things out.
要派人去处理事务

49
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:39,840
I thought that someone might be...
或许派尼克利森去？

50
00:03:39,930 --> 00:03:41,450
...Nick Leeson?
或许派尼克利森去？

51
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:50,200
Indonesia was one of the new "tiger economies"...
印度尼西亚是远东区

52
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:52,730
...everyone was getting so excited about.
新亚洲小虎经济国家

53
00:03:52,810 --> 00:03:55,490
"Emerging markets" they were calling them,...
人人都厚望霸菱对新市场

54
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:58,850
...and Barings was one of the first to see their potential.
很有兴趣

55
00:03:59,730 --> 00:04:02,480
The rewards were high. But so were the risks.
到那里报酬很高   但风险大

56
00:04:04,170 --> 00:04:06,050
One hundred million pounds...
一亿英镑

57
00:04:06,130 --> 00:04:07,800
...in bearer bonds.
一亿英镑

58
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:09,450
As good as cash.
现金

59
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:11,410
We could pick 'em up, walk out,...
我们立刻起行

60
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:14,160
...come to some arrangement with laughing boy...
无后顾之忧

61
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,130
Customers refuse to pay for them.
顾客不愿付钱

62
00:04:16,210 --> 00:04:19,200
They say what's on them doesn't match the original deal.
说协议价钱  与原本有别

63
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:22,730
The real reason: the market goes down, they don't want any more.
原因是市场下跌  他们不想负责

64
00:04:22,810 --> 00:04:24,640
It's a mess.
很难搞

65
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:29,440
You're absolutely 100 per cent right, Susi. It's one hell of a fuckin' mess.
苏慈，你说得对  真难搞

66
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,560
周日早上十时 飞机到二十哩

67
00:04:36,170 --> 00:04:38,520
It was my job to sort out the certificates...
我工作是整理证明文件

68
00:04:38,610 --> 00:04:41,880
...so customers wouldn't have any more excuses not to pay.
顾客无可抵赖

69
00:04:41,970 --> 00:04:45,850
Until then, Barings had this bloody great hole in their balance sheet.
令霸菱免受损失

70
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,960
It was boring work, but I knew if I made a success of it...
这工作很闷，但若成功...

71
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:51,000
...then I could write my own ticket.
便成真正经纪

72
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:53,960
All the certificates are in the right denomination.
所有证明文件没有错

73
00:04:54,050 --> 00:04:57,800
I've sorted out all the documentation. That's all in order now, so...
我把所有文件顺序好

74
00:04:57,890 --> 00:04:59,600
...all I need from you...
只需签发支票

75
00:04:59,690 --> 00:05:01,400
...is a cheque!
只需签发支票

76
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,190
Hello. I'm Lisa.
我是丽莎

77
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,160
I'm, um... Nick Leeson. Can I help you?
我是尼克利森   有何贵干

78
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,760
Barings sent me to help with the settlements.
霸菱派来协助你

79
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:28,400
Didn't they tell you?
没告诉你？

80
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:33,880
Oh, of course! I've been on at them for so long I never thought they'd get round to it.
当然有           是很久的事，以为他们忘了

81
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:36,270
What do we do with that lot? Build a bonfire?
那么干什么？开营火会？

82
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,670
I'd never even heard of Barings before I started working for 'em.
在霸菱工作前我没听过它的名

83
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:48,070
It's not like there's a Barings in Watford.
和华福的霸菱不同

84
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:51,760
You're a hero in London. They think the sun shines out of your arse.
你在伦敦成为英雄  他们认为你干得很好

85
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:55,910
Really? I was beginning to feel like one of those Japanese soldiers.
真的？ 感到自己像日本武士

86
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,200
Still stuck out in the jungle 20 years after the war!
二十年后从森林到现实

87
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:02,480
What's it like here? They tell me it's not safe at night.
这里是怎样？晚间外出很危险

88
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,510
Bollocks. The locals are great.
夸大，这城市很有活力

89
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:09,670
And it's not full of pompous ex-colonials thinking they were born to rule the world.
好处是不会有自大的英国人  以为这里由他们管治

90
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,590
That's what I love about Asia.
所以我爱亚洲

91
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,710
Anyone can make it. Doesn't matter which school you went to.
无论是否出自名校都有机会

92
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:19,390
When they told me I was going to Jakarta I had to look it up on the map.
当派到雅加达时   我要在地图找它呢！

93
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,670
As a matter of fact, so did I.
我也是

94
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,790
I really want to be a trader.
我想当股票经纪

95
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,830
If Barings don't let me on the floor after this, I'm off.
若霸菱不让我当经纪便离开

96
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,750
- Not gonna be bloody clerking all my life. - Ooh! Ambitious, aren't we?
不想一生当文员                       我们有野心，对吗？

97
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,750
- Is that bad? - It's great.
不好吗？          真好

98
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,670
I just want to get on in life.
我想干一番事业

99
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:40,710
I like to enjoy myself, don't get me wrong. Work hard, play hard.
我享受人生尽情工作和玩乐

100
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,150
Well, I think this is me.
我的房间

101
00:06:44,710 --> 00:06:47,350
Well, night, Nick. That was fun.
尼克，晚安          很愉快

102
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:50,700
Yeah, it was, wasn't it?
对

103
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:53,470
- OK. Night-night! - See you tomorrow, then.
好了，晚安               明天见

104
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:57,470
Lisa was a stunner all right.
丽莎真美

105
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,510
Love at first sight.
一见钟情

106
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:02,900
Together we made short work of the rest of those bonds.
我们一起很有感觉

107
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:07,270
Soon we cleared up most of Barings' losses and it was time to go home.
我们做完霸菱的呆坏帐准备回家

108
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:09,070
See you later, Lisa.
丽莎，再见

109
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:11,190
Bye.
再见

110
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:35,270
I think you'll agree that in Nick Lisa has met her prince.
尼克是丽莎心目中的王子

111
00:07:35,350 --> 00:07:36,940
Hear! Hear!
注意了

112
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:40,460
Join me in wishing them well in their new life in Singapore,...
恭祝他们在新加坡的新生活

113
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:45,220
...where Nick is to be general manager of the trading floor. Whatever that means.
尼克会是股票交易部经理

114
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:48,220
It impressed the hell out of me, but...
他表现很出色

115
00:07:48,310 --> 00:07:49,580
And, um...
尼克

116
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:52,980
To you, Nick, I'm entrusting the most precious of gifts.
我们送你珍贵的礼物

117
00:07:53,070 --> 00:07:55,900
I know you're gonna look after her and cherish her...
要好好待她爱护她

118
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:58,550
...and all those other things. And if you don't,...
比其他重要      否则

119
00:08:00,470 --> 00:08:02,700
...I'll break your bloody legs, all right?
打断你双腿

120
00:08:03,590 --> 00:08:05,100
He means it!
他认真的

121
00:08:05,790 --> 00:08:07,740
I love you so much, Lisa Leeson.
丽莎利森，我爱你

122
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:10,020
I love you too, Nick.
尼克，我也爱你

123
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:20,980
As a reward for Jakarta I'd been given the far more important market of Singapore,...
由于在雅加达很成功         所以派我到新加坡       更重要市场

124
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:24,580
...with a brief to set up my own trading operation.
在这设立运作架构

125
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:27,460
I was definitely on my way.
要全力以赴

126
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:39,860
- And the kitchen... - This is your department, darling.
厨房呢              这是新居

127
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:41,930
Since when? Cheeky!
何时入住？

128
00:08:43,420 --> 00:08:45,410
And the bedroom...
还有睡房

129
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:45,750
Yes
对

130
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:03,090
- If you need anything, call me. - Right, thanks.
若有需要，可找我          谢谢你

131
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:05,140
- Have a nice day. - Thanks. Bye.
祝你愉快         谢谢，再见

132
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:07,210
Goodbye.
再见

133
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:11,060
Not bad for a chancer from Watford, eh?
算不错吧

134
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:14,490
Well, um... I think we should test out that mattress, big boy.
先试试睡床是否舒服

135
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:16,570
- Oh, yeah? - Yeah!
要吗？    要

136
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:44,410
I can't see any problem in you handling both sides of the operation.
目前你在处理业务上并无犯错

137
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,060
- At least until volumes increase. - Right.
并数额大增             对

138
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:49,930
You shouldn't need more than two on the trading floor.
你不需超过两个助手

139
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:51,930
A couple more in the back office.
而要多个文职处理转帐

140
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:53,850
No need to pay top dollar.
无须高薪

141
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:56,690
Get them young, get them hungry and train them up.
只要年轻肯学习

142
00:09:56,770 --> 00:10:01,330
- I'm a bottom line kind of guy, Nick. - Absolutely. That's my philosophy.
尼克，简单好了                                  当然，这也是经营哲学

143
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:04,850
I took him at his word. My team were young, hungry...
如他说，我的队员很年轻

144
00:10:04,930 --> 00:10:06,650
...and they didn't have a clue.
他们好学，但对股市没经验

145
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:11,520
A futures contract allows you to buy or sell a specified amount of a commodity...
期指合约是一份    买卖合约

146
00:10:11,610 --> 00:10:14,000
...at a specified price at a future date.
在指定日期的指定价格

147
00:10:17,490 --> 00:10:19,320
Right. Um...
对

148
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:23,930
It's like, if I agree to sell you this cup of cappuccino, which I don't yet own,...
若我同意把咖啡卖给你

149
00:10:24,010 --> 00:10:26,050
...at 45 cents a month from now...
我在一个月后以四十五仙卖给你

150
00:10:26,130 --> 00:10:30,330
If I can buy the cappuccino at, say, 43 cents, I make a profit.
到时我花四十三仙买到，便赚钱

151
00:10:30,410 --> 00:10:33,720
If the price goes the other way I have to pay more, and I lose.
若价钱上升要多花钱，便是亏损

152
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:36,690
It's timing - buying and selling at the right moment.
关键就是买卖的时间

153
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:40,000
Sometimes espresso might be the best deal, or salt, or pepper.
有时咖啡最赚钱是盐或胡椒

154
00:10:40,090 --> 00:10:42,160
So, we're running a supermarket?
就像经营超级市场

155
00:10:44,370 --> 00:10:46,720
We're not buying and selling anything real.
其实没有进行真正买卖

156
00:10:46,810 --> 00:10:50,320
It's just numbers - contracts based on the value of the Nikkei,...
只是数字游戏           游戏是依照日经股票市场

157
00:10:50,410 --> 00:10:52,130
...the Tokyo stock market.
游戏是依照日经股票市场

158
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:55,560
- Er, we do this for the bank? - No, no, for the customers.
这是为银行做？                 --不，是为顾客

159
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:58,610
We are not allowed to trade on behalf of the bank.
我们不准代表银行炒卖

160
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:01,120
Be sure you remember that, all right?
要紧记这点

161
00:11:01,810 --> 00:11:05,850
Other dealers wear red jackets. All same. Red is lucky Chinese colour.
交易员全都穿着红褛    红色是中国人的幸运颜色

162
00:11:05,930 --> 00:11:09,810
Well, we want to stand out. We're a new operation. We need to be noticed.
对，所以我们要特别点    新的运作要被人注目

163
00:11:09,890 --> 00:11:11,840
May be bad luck. Different colour.
不同的颜色会带来不幸

164
00:11:11,930 --> 00:11:13,840
Bollocks. We make our own luck.
别傻，我们有彩数

165
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:17,200
Nick's right. We're cool dudes, man. Whoo!
尼克说得对，我们很帅

166
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,680
Fernando. Anything happening in Tokyo?
法兰度，东京有什么发生吗？

167
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,510
Nothin'. How's SIMEX?
没什么，新加坡市场呢？

168
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,670
Same here. No one's playin'.
一样，成交量只有五百九十

169
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,750
590, and trading small.
一样，成交量只有五百九十

170
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,640
600, and thin too.
不足六百

171
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:11,080
580 here. There's a seller who wants to trade in size. Shall I low-tick him?
五百八十，有买家想大手入市    要给低价吗？

172
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,750
Yeah. Flush him out.
好，让他买入呢

173
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:16,200
- Squeeze the sucker. - How many?
把坏人赶走              --多少？

174
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,600
200.
二百

175
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,350
Buy them... now.
现在买入

176
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,790
- Buy 'em! - Filled!
买入            --补仓

177
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:24,720
We paid 580 for 200.
你以五百八十元买入二百手

178
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:27,190
Way to go, Nick! I sold at 590.
尼克，我刚以五百九十沽货

179
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,390
Fuck a duck! Just made 2,000 quid.
该死，刚赚到二千英镑

180
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,120
Yes!
对

181
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:41,830
They were a good bunch and they were keen to learn.
他们很好学  股票经纪各施各法

182
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:47,190
It looked like a madhouse with all the traders waving and shouting,...
就像马场一样刺激

183
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:50,150
...but it all made sense once you got the hang of it.
置身其中更难忘    我干了什么？

184
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:53,310
There were hiccups, but that's normal in any operation,...
市场有起有跌     这是很正常

185
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:56,070
...especially a new one like ours.
对新人而言

186
00:12:57,520 --> 00:13:00,910
The important thing was we were picking up the business...
最重要令生意上升

187
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,990
...and the future looked rosy.
未来充满憧憬

188
00:13:15,430 --> 00:13:20,110
Nick, what's the difference between initial margin and variation margin?
尼克   单一I展和综合I展有何分别

189
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:24,150
Initial margin's a down payment on each futures contract that we trade.
单一I展是只付期指合约首期

190
00:13:24,230 --> 00:13:26,510
We don't pay in full until a contract matures.
在合约期满前也不需付全数

191
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:30,270
But in the meantime the value of each contract may go up or down.
但每份合约都会各别升跌

192
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:33,500
So SIMEX calculate our positions on a daily basis.
新加坡交易所每日计我们的交易

193
00:13:33,590 --> 00:13:37,820
They'll ask for more money if the market goes against us. That's variation margin.
当市场与投资有分差便要补仓   这叫综合I展

194
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,300
Got it. I think!
我明白了

195
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:47,070
We need to open an errors account. We've had a few mistakes.
我们要开一个记错户口  我们有点错，虽没什么，但...

196
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:50,270
I need somewhere to put them till I can write them out.
我把帐目转到那里直至填补错误

197
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:52,940
Sure. What number shall I give it?
好的，我们要什么户口号码？

198
00:13:53,030 --> 00:13:56,860
- Well, what's your lucky number? - Eight. It is a very lucky Chinese number.
你的幸运号码？               --八号，中国人喜欢八号

199
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:59,380
And how many numbers do we need?
要多少个号码

200
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:00,620
Five.
五个

201
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:04,830
Then let's give it all the luck it can handle. Call it the 88888 account.
就起个幸运号码  叫88888户口吧

202
00:14:26,430 --> 00:14:32,420
And now it gives me great pleasure to welcome the chairman of Barings Bank,...
我很荣幸为你介绍   霸菱主席

203
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,740
...Peter Baring.
彼得霸菱

204
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:45,900
We may be the oldest merchant bank in the world,...
我们是全球最悠久的银行之一

205
00:14:45,980 --> 00:14:49,940
...but that's no excuse for not keeping up with the times.
但并不代表我们过时

206
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:51,980
When I became chairman,...
当我上任主席一职后

207
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:56,450
...I realised we couldn't go on running Barings like a gentlemen's club.
我发现不可把它当成俱乐部

208
00:14:56,540 --> 00:15:00,820
We had to look beyond our traditional recruiting grounds,...
我们要打破  传统管治方法...

209
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,970
...the old school tie,...
传统学校领带

210
00:15:03,060 --> 00:15:06,130
...to seek out a new and hungrier breed.
寻求新的管理方式

211
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:11,540
We're beginning to see the fruits of those efforts, and I have to say,...
我们开始看到成效      利润...

212
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:17,410
...the recovery in profitability, since the reorganisation, has been... amazing.
更大幅回升

213
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:22,130
To be frank, I've discovered it's not actually terribly difficult...
坦白说... 在证券业务中赚取利润并不困难

214
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:24,940
...to make money in the securities business!
在证券业务中赚取利润并不困难

215
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:36,330
Filled.
补仓

216
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:48,370
Yeah, you paid 50 for 20.
对，以五十元买二十手

217
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:52,370
Come in.
进来

218
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:55,290
Simon, er... I've got a slight problem.
辛逊，我出了一点问题

219
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:59,810
One of the girls sold 20 contracts for Fuji Bank instead of buying.
有一女职员为富士银行  买入二十手，却误沽货了

220
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:02,050
I can't do anything about it till Monday.
我要周一才修补这问题

221
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:03,620
What's the damage?
损失多少

222
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:06,970
20,000 at the close.
收市时达二万

223
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:12,650
Sack the cow. She'll never work on SIMEX again.
开除她   她不可再工作

224
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,210
That's a bit hard, isn't it?
太不近人情吧！

225
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:17,330
Look, you handle it.
自己处理吧

226
00:16:17,410 --> 00:16:21,570
Have a word with London, but make sure you make that client good.
向伦敦汇报，要令客户满意

227
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:25,440
All right.
好吧

228
00:16:30,210 --> 00:16:32,170
Hey! Have a beer, shithead!
喝杯酒吧

229
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,690
Cheers.
干杯

230
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:35,680
Hi, darling.
嗨，老公

231
00:16:35,770 --> 00:16:37,970
Anyone seen Kim?
看到金吗

232
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:40,330
She was here a minute ago.
她之前还在...

233
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:47,640
Kim...
金

234
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,530
Nick, Nick...
尼克

235
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:52,600
I'm really sorry. I got so confused.
尼克，对不起

236
00:16:52,690 --> 00:16:55,680
- Everybody was shouting all at once. - That's the job.
当各人都在大喊，太混乱了

237
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:58,730
That's what it's all about, keeping a cool head.
这份工作就是要保持冷静

238
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:01,120
I'm so sorry! I'll pay you back the money.
对不起，我会赔钱给你

239
00:17:01,210 --> 00:17:05,920
Sure, Kim. Four years' salary? And if the market moves it could be even worse.
金，那是你四年的薪酬    若市场再有变动情况更糟

240
00:17:07,810 --> 00:17:09,450
Come on, come on.
来

241
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:11,490
Come on, everyone makes mistakes.
每个人都会犯错

242
00:17:12,850 --> 00:17:16,810
Look, with a bit of luck I can trade out of it on Monday, all right?
若幸运，周一定会渡过难关

243
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:21,960
Nick, I've been waiting for you while everyone else is having a good time.
尼克，我一直在等你

244
00:17:22,050 --> 00:17:24,040
- I'm going home now. - Kim!
我要回家了              --金

245
00:17:25,530 --> 00:17:27,680
Kim...!
金

246
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:36,240
- Everything all right? - Never better.
顺利吗？               --很顺利

247
00:17:37,810 --> 00:17:42,160
Why don't you let me come in and help? I can't sit around all day doing nothing.
让我到公司帮你，我不想游手好闲

248
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,240
It's not a problem, Lisa.
丽莎，不是这问题

249
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:46,840
I can handle it.
我处理得来

250
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:55,280
Fernando, how are March futures looking?
法兰度，三月的数目怎样？

251
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:59,400
- I need 20 contracts at Friday's price. - You won't get Friday's price!
我暂时没有周五价格

252
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:02,520
I should have closed off the position and taken the loss.
我应该周一开始便平仓

253
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,830
Instead, I waited for the market to change.
总比等市场变动好

254
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:07,360
It changed all right, but not the way I wanted.
它的确变动了，但不是如我所愿

255
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:11,590
Now I was stuck with a bigger loss than I could own up to. And it was all my fault.
我损失更多金钱   这是我的错

256
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,670
Nick! I hear your girl handed in her notice.
尼克，听闻你的下属金辞职了

257
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,230
Never came back. She couldn't stand the pace.
对，她受不了这些压力

258
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,960
So much for loyalty!
够仗义

259
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:23,000
- Did you make the client good? - Of course. Made a small profit, actually.
你的顾客怎么了          --还好，有一点点进帐

260
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,070
Good man.
那很好

261
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:31,950
This one's for the five eights account.
这是属于88888户口

262
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:34,080
I bought the missing contracts.
我找到了那些合约

263
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,510
60,000?
合共六万英镑吗

264
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,720
- Shh! - It was only 20 before.
之前只是二万英镑

265
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,710
And the market went the wrong way. I had to cut the loss.
当市场变坏时我便立刻沽货

266
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,760
What did Simon Jones say?
辛森钟斯说什么

267
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,800
Are you serious? He'd shut us down if he knew.
你认真的吗   若他知真相定会辞退我们

268
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:48,590
It'll be all right so long as we balance the books by the end of the month.
只要在月底能收支平衡便没问题

269
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,710
- How? - We trade on our own account...
怎可能    --我们用自己的户口进行买卖

270
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:54,870
...until we wipe out the losses, then we use money from the client account...
直至填补损失为止    我们用顾客的钱

271
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,350
...and pay it back with next month's profits.
利用下个月的利润填补给客户

272
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,000
You mean, gamble?
你要作赌注吗

273
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:02,910
Relax, Bonnie. That's all the market is.
放心，邦妮    股市就如赌场一样

274
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,190
One giant casino!
浩大之极

275
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,870
George!
佐治

276
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:17,830
I was counting on nobody looking at the books until the end of each month.
我希望无人会在月结前翻查帐目

277
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:21,910
As long as the five eights account had a nil balance on the last day of the month,...
只要88888户口在每月最后一天   显示出没有盈余

278
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,790
...no one would suspect that anything was wrong.
便不会惹人怀疑

279
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:28,110
But instead of winning back the position we made more losses,...
不但没有反转劣势反而越赌越输

280
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:32,070
...and I had to borrow more money from the client account to hide them.
我要从客户的户口   借钱来隐瞒真相

281
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:45,660
Fuckin' hell, George, what are you playing at? Get fuckin' out!
佐治，你在玩什么？滚

282
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,740
Get fuckin' out! Now!
立刻给我滚

283
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:52,620
What the hell are you playing at? Out! Get out!
你在玩什么？滚        好了

284
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:56,660
Fuckin' hell!
该死的

285
00:19:59,270 --> 00:20:02,260
- Agh. - God, you're tense. Stiff as a board.
你太紧张了

286
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:06,710
If you only knew! All cos those bastards won't let me hire proper staff.
你不明白    他们不让我聘用合适的员工

287
00:20:06,790 --> 00:20:10,390
- I thought it was going so well. - It is. It's going brilliant.
我还以为一切顺利          --不错

288
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:13,910
I just spend most of my life covering everybody else's arse.
我只是忙于收拾别人的残局

289
00:20:13,990 --> 00:20:16,900
Well, why don't you let me help with the back office?
不如让我到公司帮你吧

290
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:19,380
- I'm bored being a lady of leisure. - No.
我平时在家中呆着呢

291
00:20:19,470 --> 00:20:23,700
Why not? It's ridiculous, you having to handle trading and settlements.
尼克，为何？ 文职事业不是由你负担

292
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,700
You'll have a nervous breakdown.
你快要精神崩溃了

293
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:28,180
I don't want you interfering. I can handle it.
因为我不想你介入我可以处理的

294
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:31,940
All right, keep your pants on! No one's saying you can't.
好吧，那么你别发怒  你一定做得到

295
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:36,940
I'm not going back to being a bloody clerk. I'd rather be a plasterer.
我不回去当文员   我宁愿当抹灰匠

296
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:41,780
My mum always used to say I could be anything I wanted,...
我妈妈常说  只要有恒心，铁柱磨成针

297
00:20:41,870 --> 00:20:44,620
...so long as I took my chances - and worked like a dog.
只要肯努力

298
00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:47,980
Well, you have. You've worked really hard and it paid off.
你已经很努力了，而且还得回报

299
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:49,860
She'd have been so proud of you.
她一定为你而自豪

300
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:52,180
Do you really think so?
真的吗

301
00:20:52,670 --> 00:20:54,380
Yeah.
当然

302
00:20:54,470 --> 00:20:56,260
I know I am!
对

303
00:21:00,710 --> 00:21:04,940
That was the worst part - Lisa thinking I was this brilliant success.
最惨的是丽莎以为我是天才

304
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:08,980
If she only knew what a fuck-up I really was!
她并不知道我其实很不济

305
00:21:09,060 --> 00:21:11,500
When I wanted the market to go up, it went down.
当我想股市上升时它便下跌

306
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:13,650
If I wanted it to go down, it went up.
我想它下跌它却又上升

307
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:16,500
It was hard not to take it personally.
这真难缠

308
00:21:25,940 --> 00:21:27,420
Nick?
尼克？

309
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:30,860
Nick! I just worked out the balance in the eights account.
我刚计算了88888的收支平衡

310
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:34,700
- The losses are over $10 million! - Keep your fuckin' voice down!
我们损失了超过一千万元        --邦妮，别这么大声

311
00:21:34,780 --> 00:21:36,770
Look, there's no need to panic.
也不用那么慌张

312
00:21:37,860 --> 00:21:42,330
There's not enough in the client account to make margin payments, Nick.
客户的帐户不够钱填补I展欠款

313
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:47,130
Right.
没错

314
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:54,220
I need dollars. I need dollars to cover the initial margin payment!
我需要钱填补最初的I展欠款

315
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:59,570
I can get dollars from London to cover all the client positions for the futures I buy!
我叫伦敦汇钱给我填补这些损失

316
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:03,370
Nothing unusual about that. But I'm gonna need yen.
这样也不是罕见       但我需要日圆

317
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:06,500
Gonna need yen to cover the daily variation columns!
以便在月底前

318
00:22:06,580 --> 00:22:09,770
Which'll leave a yen deficit by the end of the month.
填补所损失的日圆

319
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:13,130
Unless... unless I sell options.
除非... 我沽售期权来换取日圆佣金

320
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:15,930
That'll generate commission in yen.
我沽售期权来换取日圆佣金

321
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:20,620
And return the balance sheet on the five eights account to zero!
将88888户口维持零进帐

322
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:27,810
As long as London kept sending out money to finance the client positions,...
只要我能说服伦敦总公司汇钱

323
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:31,370
...I'd have enough cash to stay on top of the margin payments.
给我填补损失

324
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,570
It was like robbing Peter to pay Paul,...
这只是亡羊补牢

325
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:40,370
...but hopefully I'd end up making enough to pay Peter back before he found out.
但我希望赚到足够的金钱 给我填补损失

326
00:22:40,450 --> 00:22:45,080
Meanwhile I had to generate more and more business to justify my cash calls,...
其间  我要找更多生意来证明

327
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:47,320
...and for that I needed customers.
我是为顾客利益要求现金资助

328
00:22:48,610 --> 00:22:50,600
The bigger the better.
越多越好

329
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:01,160
Mm-hm. Oui.
好

330
00:23:05,130 --> 00:23:06,850
Mr Leeson.
利森先生...

331
00:23:06,930 --> 00:23:09,370
- I'm Pierre Beaumarchais. - Nice to meet you.
我是彼亚波马斯          --很高兴认识你

332
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:12,680
I work for the Geneva Banking Trust, based in the Bahamas.
我以巴哈马为基地的日内瓦银行工作

333
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:16,760
I was speaking with Ang Swee Tian, president of SIMEX.
我刚兴新加坡交易市所总裁  安维田谈话

334
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:20,370
He's impressed by the amount of business you've been generating.
因你为他赚取的生意额感满意

335
00:23:20,450 --> 00:23:23,040
- There's a lot of opportunities here. - Oh, yes.
外边有很多机会           --就是

336
00:23:24,090 --> 00:23:26,080
I do a lot of business on SIMEX.
我在新加坡市场也参与很多交易

337
00:23:26,650 --> 00:23:28,840
With the exception of George Soros,...
除了佐治罗索斯

338
00:23:28,930 --> 00:23:31,840
...I probably trade in the Nikkei more than anyone.
我在日经市场的投资比任何人多

339
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:35,000
Sometimes over 5,000 contracts in a day.
一日通常高达五千张合约

340
00:23:35,090 --> 00:23:38,520
That is a lot. The whole market only does about 20.
整个市场的成交量只有二十左右

341
00:23:39,810 --> 00:23:42,880
Could Barings handle that amount of business?
霸菱可以处理这么大的生意吗

342
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:48,280
You bet we could!
当然可以

343
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:50,930
Beaumarchais was the answer to my prayers.
波马斯是我的救星

344
00:23:51,010 --> 00:23:53,570
I'd be able to siphon off enough commission...
我利用当中所得的佣金

345
00:23:53,650 --> 00:23:56,960
...to square the eights account once and for all.
一次过填补88888户口的损失

346
00:23:58,170 --> 00:24:00,360
- Hello? - Pierre Beaumarchais.
彼亚波马斯

347
00:24:00,450 --> 00:24:02,960
I want to buy 4,000 June contracts.
我想买四千张六月份的合约

348
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:07,200
I've... got a price of 350, but this'll move it.
目前的价格是三百五十  但股价不断变动

349
00:24:07,290 --> 00:24:09,800
Try not to pay more than 400.
升幅别超过四百元

350
00:24:09,890 --> 00:24:12,720
We gotta get them cheap. Beaumarchais is a big player.
我们低水入货  波马斯是大玩家

351
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:15,400
If we pull this off, we get a shitload of business.
若我们讨得他欢心便不愁没生意

352
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:18,040
- What's liquidity like? - Tight as a flea's arse.
流动资产如何          --只有很少

353
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:20,800
We'll get away with 500, then the price will move up.
我们在五百点沽货 之后股市上升

354
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:24,160
OK. But then we'll make the other traders think we're sellers.
要令其他交易家以为我们要沽货

355
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,550
And when the price drops... buy! All right?
到股价下跌时再买入

356
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,240
OK.
好的

357
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,200
Sell 250!
二百五十点沽货

358
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:41,000
Sell 250! Sell 250!
二百五十点沽货

359
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,830
Sell 240!
二百五十点沽货

360
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:43,610
Sell 240! Sell 240!
二百四十点沽货

361
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:45,440
Sell 240! Sell 240!
二百四十点沽货

362
00:24:44,010 --> 00:24:45,040
Sell 240! Sell 240!
二百四十点沽货

363
00:24:45,780 --> 00:24:46,770
Sell 240! Sell 240!
二百四十点沽货

364
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:49,980
Sell 200! Sell 200!
二百点沽货

365
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:53,000
Sell 200! Sell 200!
二百点沽货

366
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:53,110
Sell 200! Sell 200!
二百点沽货

367
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,350
- Buy 500 contracts! - Sell 200!
买五百手         --二百点沽货

368
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,160
Buy? Buy?
要买吗

369
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:05,200
Buy at 200! Buy at 200! Buy at 210!
在二百点买入

370
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,270
Buy at 210! Buy at 220!
在二百一十点买入

371
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:10,670
Buy at 220! Buy at 230!
在二百二点买入

372
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:14,280
Buy at 240!
在二百一十点买入

373
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,350
Buy at 240! Buy at 240!
在二百一十点买入

374
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,640
Filled!
弄好

375
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:30,230
Nobody saw us coming! We swooped on the first 1500 like a Stealth bomber!
没人估计到我们的策略       我们转眼赚了一百五十万

376
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,150
4,000 contracts!
四千手

377
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:35,230
Balls of steel, Fat Boy. Balls of fuckin' steel!
肥仔，快点买

378
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:56,950
At last my luck had changed. Suddenly I couldn't stop making money.
我终于行运了  我突然停不了赚大钱

379
00:25:57,670 --> 00:26:01,830
I was long in the Nikkei - that meant gambling on it going up - and up it went.
对准日经平均指数的走势    在炒股生意上取得优势  上落尽在我掌握之中

380
00:26:02,910 --> 00:26:04,900
Up and up and up.
股市继续上升

381
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:12,870
That's very good! Very good.
尼克，干得好

382
00:26:15,150 --> 00:26:17,140
Serves you right, Lisa!
加班

383
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:35,180
If it went all the way up to 19,000, I stood to make a killing on the options I'd sold.
若指数继续上升至一万九千点  我沽售所有期权后一定赚大钱

384
00:26:38,590 --> 00:26:42,030
Come on, come on! Come on, baby, you can do it. Come on.
来吧...快

385
00:26:43,670 --> 00:26:45,660
- Yes! - Yes!
好

386
00:26:49,590 --> 00:26:53,060
Bonnie, we're on a fuckin' roll!
邦妮，我们成功了

387
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:55,140
Yes!
是的

388
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:58,020
Do you think we'll do it?
我还以为功亏一篑

389
00:27:05,470 --> 00:27:08,140
It's amazing! You've made back all the losses.
神奇，你填补了超过...

390
00:27:08,230 --> 00:27:12,460
- Over $10 million. - What did I tell you? Oh, ye of little faith!
一千万元的损失           --我说过要有信心

391
00:27:12,550 --> 00:27:15,260
You keep doubling up, and sooner or later...
你继续加倍入货很快我们便赚钱

392
00:27:15,350 --> 00:27:17,380
...you're bound to win.
你继续加倍入货很快我们便赚钱

393
00:27:22,430 --> 00:27:25,380
The Nikkei has closed up for the third day in a row,...
日经平均指数连续第三日停市

394
00:27:25,460 --> 00:27:28,900
...and the rally shows little sign of running out of steam.
日经平均指数连续第三日停市

395
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:32,450
Analysts are predicting additional gains in the days ahead.
但没迹象显示会炒风过热...

396
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:43,620
- Happy? - Yeah. Are you?
开心吗             你呢？

397
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:45,530
Never better.
从未如此开心过

398
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:52,380
I have been sailing a bit close to the wind. I didn't want to worry you with it.
最初时损失了一点   但我不想令你担心

399
00:27:53,020 --> 00:27:55,170
- What do you mean? - No, it's all right.
你说什么    没什么

400
00:27:55,260 --> 00:27:58,780
The market turned round and a whole load of my positions came good.
市场改变，让我填补了损失

401
00:27:58,860 --> 00:28:00,740
I made it all back.
市场改变，让我填补了损失

402
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:02,810
What are you on about, Nick?
你怎么了

403
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:08,380
Don't get your knickers in a twist, but we made mistakes and ran up some losses.
别担心，我只是犯了一点错

404
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:10,850
I went out on a limb to get back the position.
所以我要赌一赌把钱赚回来

405
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:12,770
How big were the losses?
你损失多少

406
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:16,370
- It's about a million. - A million quid?!
大约一百万                      一百万英镑？

407
00:28:17,140 --> 00:28:19,130
For God's sake, Nick!
尼克，你太过分

408
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:23,490
No, it's all right. It paid off. I squared it up.
没事了，已经赚回来

409
00:28:24,020 --> 00:28:26,010
I had to do it to protect the guys.
我要保护我的下属

410
00:28:28,260 --> 00:28:30,770
Promise me that you'll never do that again.
答应我不要再这样干

411
00:28:30,860 --> 00:28:33,420
- It's not worth it, Nick. - I promise.
你不值得这样做    我答应你

412
00:28:35,220 --> 00:28:37,210
You will give me a heart attack.
你快把我吓得心脏病发

413
00:28:42,020 --> 00:28:44,770
- Merry Christmas. - Merry Christmas.
圣诞快乐

414
00:28:52,580 --> 00:28:54,570
Fuck off!
该死

415
00:28:56,660 --> 00:29:01,330
I really meant it. I was the number one trader, and as the new year came in...
我认真的   我是城中最成功交易员

416
00:29:01,410 --> 00:29:04,770
...I was determined to kick my addiction to the eights account.
踏入新年，我决要    好好利用88888户口

417
00:29:04,850 --> 00:29:06,730
What will the market do? Long-term?
你认为应长线    投资吗？

418
00:29:06,810 --> 00:29:09,490
No one thinks long-term, they think nanoseconds!
你说笑吧，没人会考虑长线投资

419
00:29:09,570 --> 00:29:12,250
- Long-term's tomorrow morning. - Tomorrow, then.
长线就是明天    就依你所说的

420
00:29:12,330 --> 00:29:16,090
- That would be telling. - Leeson speaks, the market moves!
一言为定    利森的举动足以令市场变动

421
00:29:16,170 --> 00:29:18,160
You said it, mate.
一言为定

422
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:20,410
Pierre.
彼亚

423
00:29:20,490 --> 00:29:24,800
I want to sell the 220 call options and buy the 200 calls in December.
我要沽二百二十手看涨期权  在十二月买入二百手涨期权

424
00:29:24,890 --> 00:29:27,930
I've got an offer of .138 for size.
你会有一点三八巴仙的佣金

425
00:29:28,010 --> 00:29:29,890
Can you do better?
你做得到吗

426
00:29:29,970 --> 00:29:31,610
I'll get back to you.
我再联络你

427
00:29:31,690 --> 00:29:34,290
Quick as you can, Nick. I have to move fast.
尼克，我们要速战速决

428
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:40,970
What the hell is he on about, .138 for size?
什么？谁人会出这个价钱

429
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:44,330
The market in 220 calls is down. He wants to cut his losses.
沽二百二十手会亏蚀的   我们要为客人止蚀

430
00:29:44,410 --> 00:29:47,080
- Yeah, but why .138? - It's a ratio.
为何出这价钱？         他们以百分率计算

431
00:29:47,170 --> 00:29:49,440
The 200 calls are trading at 1,400.
以二百手换一千四百手

432
00:29:49,530 --> 00:29:53,410
Divide 200 by 1,400, you get .143.
你便可以获得  一点四三巴仙的佣金

433
00:29:53,490 --> 00:29:55,880
All right. But not .138.
但不是一点三八巴仙的佣金

434
00:29:56,410 --> 00:30:00,320
Unless someone's offered him a discount. Probably Societe Generale.
除非有人给他折扣  彼亚是我们主要的客户

435
00:30:00,410 --> 00:30:03,160
We can't let those wankers get our biggest client.
不能损失这个客人

436
00:30:03,250 --> 00:30:05,720
- What are you gonna do? - Just have to leg it.
你打算怎样             我们一定要帮他

437
00:30:05,810 --> 00:30:09,360
Buy the contracts from Pierre and sell them when the market rises?
你是说向彼亚买入那期股票             然后趁高沽货

438
00:30:09,450 --> 00:30:12,440
I thought we were not supposed to trade for the bank.
我们不应为银行作买卖

439
00:30:12,530 --> 00:30:14,480
Pierre? I can do it. What's the exact size?
彼亚，我可帮你，有多少期货

440
00:30:14,570 --> 00:30:17,290
6,500? All right, leave it with me. No problem.
六千五百？等我来处理

441
00:30:18,010 --> 00:30:21,120
What if the market doesn't rise, uh? What if it falls?
若股市下跌不上升那怎办

442
00:30:21,210 --> 00:30:24,600
I've gambled and won before. I can gamble and win again.
我曾赌博胜了，一定可以再赢

443
00:30:24,690 --> 00:30:28,310
Balls of steel, me old mateys, and you'd better believe it.
我是神奇小子，你要信我

444
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:42,200
Bonnie, I need you to reopen the eights account.
邦妮        你再为我开启88888户口

445
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,160
We got caned on Beaumarchais' contracts.
我们被那些波马斯的股票害死

446
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:48,520
Now the bastard's gone back to Societe Generale.
那些混旦找中央股票行帮他们

447
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:52,880
Fax Brenda Granger in London. Ask her for funds to cover the margin payments.
你传真给佩达   叫她多点资金以应付I展款项

448
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,950
Tell her it's for client positions.
说是为了她的客户

449
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:56,920
Hello?
你好

450
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,120
It's Simon. Can you come into my office?
尼克，我是辛逊  到我办公室，

451
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:00,680
Right away.
有事找你

452
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:04,910
Christ, I'd been rumbled! The only surprise was it'd taken so long.
一定是出事   终于被揭发

453
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:08,070
What was I gonna tell Lisa? She'd bloody murder me.
我怎告诉丽莎？她定会宰了我

454
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,150
Come in.
进来

455
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:17,750
Congratulations, Nick.
尼克，恭喜你

456
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:21,230
The '93 bonuses are in, and you're down for 135 grand.
九三年的花红发放了          你有一三五万

457
00:31:22,560 --> 00:31:24,790
135? That's fantastic!
一三五？真不错

458
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:30,590
Your little operation generated profits of over 10 million last year. You're a star!
去年为公司赚了超过一千万英镑   你是我们的明星

459
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,790
In fact, your figures are so high they're going to check up on you.
因为你赚了巨额数目   所以他们要核数

460
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:37,760
Check up on me?
查核我的帐目？

461
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:40,800
They're sending Ash Lewis out for the audit.
他们派艾斯路易斯来

462
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:44,960
Don't worry. It's purely routine.
别担心，只是例行工作

463
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:46,990
Ash Lewis?
艾斯路易斯？

464
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:49,830
She's meant to be a right ball-breaker, isn't she?
男人见到她便怕

465
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:59,430
That's our booth.
那是我们展览摊位

466
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:03,190
Filled! You paid 250.
全都满了，你付二百五十

467
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,110
Hi, Nick.
尼克

468
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,190
Ron Baker and Ash Lewis.
这是朗伯嘉，他是艾斯路易斯

469
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:09,660
Ron is head of Derivatives Trading in London.
朗是负责伦敦市场的主管

470
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,790
Which I guess makes me your boss, Nick.
我便是你的上司

471
00:32:11,870 --> 00:32:14,710
- How do you, Mr Leeson? - Very well, thank you.
很高兴认识你    利森先生，你好吗   很好，谢谢

472
00:32:14,790 --> 00:32:16,860
OK Let's see the action!
我们开始工作

473
00:32:18,950 --> 00:32:20,100
Henry!
亨利

474
00:32:20,190 --> 00:32:23,580
Who's doing all the business? We're the biggest, right?
谁负责这主意？我们最大的

475
00:32:23,670 --> 00:32:26,590
We do a lot of arbitrage, so we do have a high volume.
我们为客人处理套利活动   所以交易量很大

476
00:32:26,670 --> 00:32:29,510
We signal orders in to George in the pit - this is Henry -
我们把所有交易通知佐治

477
00:32:29,810 --> 00:32:31,860
...and at the end of the day the girls in the office
这是亨利，每天收市后

478
00:32:32,050 --> 00:32:34,220
they log all the deals on to the computer.
公司女同事便用电脑纪录交易

479
00:32:34,710 --> 00:32:39,100
You manage the trading floor and the settlements office, is that right?
你是交易场内的经理，对吗

480
00:32:39,190 --> 00:32:41,020
Yes, yes.
亨利，你在一百的位置加了记号

481
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:45,100
That's a little unusual. Whatever happened to checks and balances?
这是比较罕见的  谁负责审查收支平衡

482
00:32:45,190 --> 00:32:49,100
- That's something we need to talk about. - I'll be here for three weeks.
这方面我们要详细汇报             我会留在这里三周

483
00:32:49,190 --> 00:32:53,070
This is going to be a thoroughly comprehensive audit. No stone unturned.
今次是详尽的审核            每一项都会审核

484
00:32:53,150 --> 00:32:57,700
Absolutely. Anything I can do to help, any stone needs turning, let me know.
当然，我会尽力提供协助          有什么发现便告诉我

485
00:32:57,790 --> 00:32:59,670
Are we filled? Good man, Henry.
我们完成了吗？亨利

486
00:32:59,750 --> 00:33:01,550
Nice to see you, Simon.
辛逊，很高兴见到你

487
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:08,540
Dad's seen this flat in Blackheath.
爸爸认为值得投资在黑希

488
00:33:08,630 --> 00:33:11,900
Needs a bit of work, but him and my granddad can fix it up.
那房屋需要修葺         但爸和祖父可负责

489
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:15,300
Think of it like an insurance policy in case you get sacked,...
如被开除，可当是一项保险

490
00:33:15,390 --> 00:33:19,180
...have to go back to England and work as a plasterer!
回英国你可当抹灰工人

491
00:33:20,950 --> 00:33:23,020
What's up with you, misery-guts?
怎么了？

492
00:33:24,430 --> 00:33:28,340
What would you do, Lise ? What would you do if I did get the elbow?
丽莎，你干什么            若我失业你干什么

493
00:33:28,430 --> 00:33:31,300
You've just been given a ruddy great big bonus.
你刚收到丰厚的花红

494
00:33:31,390 --> 00:33:35,350
But what if it all went wrong? What if I'm not as clever as everyone thinks?
若突然出现问题？         我不是别人所想的聪明

495
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:37,260
Oh, of course you are!
你当然是

496
00:33:37,990 --> 00:33:41,140
Anyway, it's you I love. I don't give a toss about the money.
我爱不是你的钱财

497
00:33:41,230 --> 00:33:45,940
If it was up to me we'd jack it all in now, go back to England and start a family.
希望立刻回英国建立我们的家庭

498
00:33:46,980 --> 00:33:49,050
You're doing brilliantly, Nick.
尼克，你很聪明

499
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:51,980
You're a bloody star.
你真聪明

500
00:34:04,860 --> 00:34:06,770
- Nick! - Fuck!
尼克？    该死

501
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:08,300
Simon!
辛逊

502
